Conan CMakeDeps generator does not support generating find modules for components of a package.
This patch fixes the situation by using the generated Conan CMakeDeps config cmake file,
so that the find_package(iceoryx) call will work correctly.

The Conan generate CMakeConfigDeps is capable of generating a cmake config file per component.

This is a custom patch produced by Conan Center Index.

--- a/src/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -134,9 +134,8 @@ if(ENABLE_ICEORYX)
   else()
     set(iceoryx_required QUIET)
   endif()
-  find_package(iceoryx_hoofs ${iceoryx_required})
-  find_package(iceoryx_posh ${iceoryx_required})
-  if(${iceoryx_hoofs_FOUND} AND ${iceoryx_posh_FOUND})
+  find_package(iceoryx ${iceoryx_required})
+  if(${iceoryx_FOUND})
     set(ENABLE_ICEORYX "ON")
   else()
     set(ENABLE_ICEORYX "OFF")
